<https://w3id.org/geko/#> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Ontology> .
<https://w3id.org/geko/#> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionIRI> <https://w3id.org/geko/v2/#> .
<https://w3id.org/geko/#> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/creator> <https://orcid.org/0009-0003-0559-0409> .
<https://w3id.org/geko/#> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "GEkO Ontology describes the phenomenon of ekphrasis along with technical implementation of image-text relations using annotations."@en .
<https://w3id.org/geko/#> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "GEkO Ontology v2" .
<https://w3id.org/geko/#> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#priorVersion> <https://w3id.org/geko/v1/#> .
<https://w3id.org/geko/#> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInfo> "2.0.0" .
<https://w3id.org/geko/#> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#changeNote> "**Version 2 Changelog** Introduction of four aspects: - hasForm ObjectProperty deprecated; NotionalEkphrasis and MimeticEkphrasis classes become subClassOf Ekphrasis - Aligment of Ekphrasis with CIDOC-CRM instantiated as subClassOf E33_Linguistic_Object - Transition to SKOS Concept to identify the ekphrastic modelities (denotation, dynamization, integration), prior modeled as classes - Definition of an ObjectProperty hasAuthor for signaling the author of Ekphrasis, more specifical than dct:creator"@en .
